-- Wells Fargo profit rises 14 pct as costs fall
-- By Anil D'Silva in Bangalore
-- Fri Apr 11, 2014 08:10AM EDT
-- None



April 11 (Reuters) - Wells Fargo & Co <WFC.N>, the biggest U.S. mortgage lender, reported a 14 percent rise in first-quarter net profit as costs fell.

Net income applicable to common shareholders rose to $5.60 billion, or $1.05 per share, in the quarter ended March 31 from $4.93 billion, or 92 cents per share, a year earlier, the fourth-biggest U.S. bank said on Friday. [ID:nBw5Cc0FMa]